body:
@himanshug we already have a build-time dependency for antlr that's used for the toy sql grammar I wrote a while back. We could use antlr to remove all the boilerplate code and reduce the chance of bugs. I think it would make it easier to extend / understand for other folks, and remove a lot of boilerplate code.
Here's what the sql one looked like:
https://github.com/druid-io/druid/blob/master/server/src/main/antlr4/io/druid/sql/antlr4/DruidSQL.g4

@himanshug that seems a bit brittle, as the coordinator could be down / slow (for a while our coordinators actually took longer than `druid.manager.segments.pollDuration` to poll the metadata store, due to poor tuning…)

I think this feature will be hard to use unless we can make it idempotent.

Maybe we can make it idempotent by rather than having people provide "intervals", instead they provide specific segments. They could potentially get these from checking for the currently active segments.
